[start section id="$final"]
Final Diagnosis
A.  Colon, left, segmental resection:  Invasive grade 4 (of 4) adenocarcinoma, forming a 5.5 x 4.5 x 0.8 cm polypoid and centrally ulcerated mass in the descending colon located 4.0 cm from the distal mucosal margin.  The tumor invades through the muscularis propria into the pericolic fat.  The surgical resection margins are negative for  tumor. Multiple (3 of 18) regional lymph nodes are positive for metastatic carcinoma.

With available surgical materials, [AJCC pT3N1](7th edition, 2010).



[end section id="$final"]
[start section id="$gross"]

Gross Description
A.  Received fresh labeled ""left segmental colon"" is a left hemicolectomy specimen consisting of 36.5 cm in length portion of colon.  There is a 5.5 x 4.5 x 0.8 cm polypoid mass within the descending colon, 4.0 cm from the distal mucosal margin.  Grossly, the mass extends into the pericolonic fat.  Multiple lymph nodes are identified within the mesenteric fat.  Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by STCYR.



Frozen Sect-Intraop
A.  Colon, left, segmental resection:  Invasive carcinoma.  Margins are negative.  HOLD to assess lymph nodes on permanent sections.  

Frozen section histologic interpretation performed by:  Francis J. Baumgartner, M.D.





[end section id="$gross"]